## Variant ID lookup (product cards / `card-context-variant-id`)

Do not use `product.variants | find: 'id', id | plus: 0` with IDs from `card-context-variant-id` or other captures. Coercing large Shopify GIDs through numeric filters can fail to match, so price, gallery, title, quick-add, and picker fall back to the wrong variant.

**Do:** compare string forms in a loop:

```liquid
assign _want = captured_variant_id | strip
assign _resolved = nil
for v in product.variants
  assign _vid_s = v.id | append: ''
  if _vid_s == _want
    assign _resolved = v
    break
  endif
endfor
```

**Collection context:** Inside blocks/snippets that use `closest.product`, the global `collection` may be unset. Pass `current_collection` into `card-context-variant-id` using `collection`, then `closest.collection` as fallback (same pattern as `variant-swatches.liquid`). Pass `scope_collection` into `collection-theme-sku-layout-active` from the same resolved collection so themed layout rules stay on for nested renders.

**Radio groups on product cards:** Use a radio `name` that includes the product id, the owning block id, and (when the same product can appear on multiple cards) the scoped collection id—e.g. `variant-main-picker` suffix `-coll{{ collection.id }}` and `variant-swatches` suffix `-b{{ block.id }}-coll{{ collection.id }}`. Otherwise multiple cards share one HTML radio group and only the first row behaves correctly.

**Theme value order + Swatches block:** The horizontal swatch row is rendered by `blocks/swatches.liquid` → `variant-swatches`. If Theme value order is only set on the Variant picker, leave the Swatches block’s same field blank so `resolve-variant-picker-priority-theme-line` can reuse the picker’s list; otherwise the swatch row keeps default order.
